From 35eea7e22f94d64c5d34d609565bc10611193895 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilya Gulya <ilya@gulya.me>
Date: Thu, 11 Jun 2026 04:04:46 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] SDK: add SDKSettings.json so Homebrew can detect the macOS
 SDK

Homebrew's SDK locator (os/mac/sdk.rb read_sdk_version) only parses
SDKSettings.JSON; our bundled MacOSX.sdk shipped only SDKSettings.plist, so
MacOS.sdk resolved to nil and every 'brew install --build-from-source' failed
the diagnostic.rb check_if_supported_sdk_available gate with 'Your CLT does not
support macOS 11. It is either outdated or was modified.'

Add a minimal SDKSettings.json declaring Version 11.3 (matching the macOS 11
userland Darling emulates) so the SDK is discoverable. The headers remain the
existing set; this only makes the SDK visible to Homebrew's scanner.

Part of making Homebrew source builds work under Darling (dar-pk4).
---
 .../Developer/SDKs/MacOSX.sdk/SDKSettings.json        | 11 +++++++++++
 1 file changed, 11 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 Developer/Platforms/MacOSX.platform/Developer/SDKs/MacOSX.sdk/SDKSettings.json

diff --git a/Developer/Platforms/MacOSX.platform/Developer/SDKs/MacOSX.sdk/SDKSettings.json b/Developer/Platforms/MacOSX.platform/Developer/SDKs/MacOSX.sdk/SDKSettings.json
new file mode 100644
index 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000..5549de4d1c967a446b2a2b5b86806066918aa3bf
--- /dev/null
+++ b/Developer/Platforms/MacOSX.platform/Developer/SDKs/MacOSX.sdk/SDKSettings.json
@@ -0,0 +1,11 @@
+{
+  "CanonicalName": "macosx11.3",
+  "DisplayName": "macOS 11.3",
+  "MinimalDisplayName": "11.3",
+  "Version": "11.3",
+  "MaximumDeploymentTarget": "11.3",
+  "DefaultDeploymentTarget": "11.3",
+  "DefaultProperties": {
+    "PLATFORM_NAME": "macosx"
+  }
+}

From b8b186a6e31c2b1cf63f8946c7b170b4a75ae794 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilya Gulya <ilya@gulya.me>
Date: Thu, 11 Jun 2026 06:14:07 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] SDK: rename versioned SDK symlink MacOSX10.13.sdk ->
 MacOSX11.sdk

The bundled MacOSX.sdk now declares Version 11.3 (75437f43b), but the
versioned discovery symlink still carried the old 10.13 name. Homebrew's
check_broken_sdks (extend/os/mac/diagnostic.rb) scans MacOSX*.sdk and fails
fatally when a versioned SDK folder name's major version disagrees with its
SDKSettings.json content version (10 != 11). Rename the symlink so the name
matches the 11.3 content. The unversioned MacOSX.sdk (used by the build via
DARLING_SDK_RELATIVE_PATH) is unaffected; no source references the 10.13
name. Mirrors the fix already applied to the CLT test prefix.

Part of dar-pk4 (Homebrew source builds out of the box).
---
 .../Platforms/MacOSX.platform/Developer/SDKs/MacOSX10.13.sdk     | 1 -
 Developer/Platforms/MacOSX.platform/Developer/SDKs/MacOSX11.sdk  | 1 +
 2 files changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)
 delete mode 120000 Developer/Platforms/MacOSX.platform/Developer/SDKs/MacOSX10.13.sdk
 create mode 120000 Developer/Platforms/MacOSX.platform/Developer/SDKs/MacOSX11.sdk

diff --git a/Developer/Platforms/MacOSX.platform/Developer/SDKs/MacOSX10.13.sdk b/Developer/Platforms/MacOSX.platform/Developer/SDKs/MacOSX10.13.sdk
deleted file mode 120000
index 36876e3682a09e3a4201bddeff9dc6619c2ffc38..0000000000000000000000000000000000000000
--- a/Developer/Platforms/MacOSX.platform/Developer/SDKs/MacOSX10.13.sdk
+++ /dev/null
@@ -1 +0,0 @@
-MacOSX.sdk/
\ No newline at end of file
diff --git a/Developer/Platforms/MacOSX.platform/Developer/SDKs/MacOSX11.sdk b/Developer/Platforms/MacOSX.platform/Developer/SDKs/MacOSX11.sdk
new file mode 120000
index 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000..36876e3682a09e3a4201bddeff9dc6619c2ffc38
--- /dev/null
+++ b/Developer/Platforms/MacOSX.platform/Developer/SDKs/MacOSX11.sdk
@@ -0,0 +1 @@
+MacOSX.sdk/
\ No newline at end of file
